Officially 34 weeks! 🤰🏻

(Pregnancy Update) 
* Baby boy is very active and loves extending his legs up in my rib cage. 😂 
* I’m thankful my night sleep is good & feeling somewhat well rested, aside from the many bathroom breaks. 
* My skin is NOT loving this pregnancy, so I do struggle with eczema / extreme sensitive skin which is the most uncomfortable part about pregnancy but I am managing.. especially since we are so close to the end. 🥰
* We bought all the final baby things so I can begin nesting and preparing for babies arrival. Only 6 weeks left until his due date! 🥹

after long hours of laboring and ending up with an emergency c-section. we are overjoyed to finally have our baby in our arms, he is so perfect. this labor and delivery was the complete opposite from my “birth plan”, but this was our incredible journey to make sure he arrived safe and sound. i’m so thankful to have had such a great labor & delivery team who took the best of care of us. in meantime thank you everyone who reached out and congratulated us. this is such a blissful time and we are soaking it all in. 🤍

Being your mama is the best thing that’s ever happened to me. I can’t wait to watch you grow, but don’t grow up too fast. 🥹 #newborn #1monthold #postpartum

1 month postpartum and I’m feeling really good! Recovery is going well thanks to my @mamawayusa belly band. After my emergency C-section, I’m lacking a lot of support in my lower back and need to add counter pressure to my incision which helps minimize any pain I’m experiencing during recovery. This belly band evenly distributes the support all around, I love the double straps feature, so I can control where I need more support. The material is very stretchy and breathable making it comfortable for all day (or night) wear. All soon to be mamas, bring this with you to the hospital and you can start wearing it right away! 

#mamawayusa #bellyband #bellywrap

The best 2 months of my life. Tommy baby, you bring us so much joy. Your cooing and smiles make my heart melt. 🫠🥹🫶🏼 #2months #9weeks
Happy Mothers Day! 🫶🏼
I just know I’m living in some of the best days of my life. I will hold onto these memories so close to my heart. 🥹 Happy 3 months my little guy. 🫶🏼

My bb is 4 months today. 😍 aside from sleep regression and teething, this has been such a sweet age. Tommy learned to roll over, tries to sit up and discovered his hands and feet. It’s so fun watching him achieve these milestones. I just can’t get enough of him, we LOVE snuggling and kissing him, it’s just the best. 🥹 #4monthsold

5 months 🤩

I am fully in my ✨mom✨era, I came to the realization my career can wait, and being a mother is my greatest calling in this season. I am thoroughly enjoying motherhood, yes it has its hard moments and the days may seem so long but man oh man the joy that comes is so fulfilling! I miss creating content and being more consistent on here but I realized that Tommy needs me and he won’t be this little forever. 😭 These are my best days, creating memories with my family.

6 months 🫶🏼 

My sweet boy. 
Tommy is ready to start crawling any day now, he is using his big boy high chair and we officially started baby led weaning. (Watermelon was his first food he tried 😂) As you can tell he loves playing with his toes and puts everything in his mouth. He is my ultimate joy, love seeing his little personality shine through. Also, can you believe it’s been half a year already? I sometimes still can’t fathom im a mom. 😂

Tommy is 7 months! I can’t believe how fast the time is going, my baby is growing up. 🥲 He is crawling around, getting into things, loves digging through bags and baskets, grabbing anything arms reach - I cannot let this boy out of my sight! 😅So many new experiences this month, swinging at the park, sitting in shopping carts, loves to observe people from all around but will sometimes get stranger danger haha. I love him so much, what an honor it is to be his mother. 💛
